  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>22:10 -!- ybit [~<a href="mailto:quassel@unaffiliated">quassel@unaffiliated</a>/ybit] has joined #openhatch
22:10 &lt; ybit&gt; interested in sci apps that need help
22:10  * ybit searches around
22:11 &lt; ybit&gt; more specifically, comp.chem 
22:11 &lt; ybit&gt; or comp.phys or comp.geom

OpenHatch helps you find projects by language, bug size, and bug type, and you can find individual 
bugs by searching on a keyword, but you can't find projects by tag or keyword search.

One could imagine: a) giving project pages a place to add tags, b) having a tag cloud somewhere for 
people to quickly browse common tag options, and c) the addition of keywords/tags to the /search 
search.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
